02:41.361 --> 02:43.697
I've always dreamed
of going to Vegas.

02:44.998 --> 02:46.633
Well, dream on
because we're taking

02:46.667 --> 02:47.668
the refrigerator.

02:50.871 --> 02:53.740
What's wrong with Vegas?

02:53.774 --> 02:54.941
Are you kidding?

02:54.975 --> 02:56.877
Vegas is‐is a moral wasteland.

02:56.910 --> 02:59.245
It goes against everything
I was ever told I believe in.

03:02.583 --> 03:03.584
When were you in Vegas?

03:03.617 --> 03:05.385
Well, I, um‐um‐uh..
Never.

03:06.687 --> 03:07.854
But I saw "Ocean's Eleven."

03:09.489 --> 03:10.657
All Vegas is‐is gambling

03:10.691 --> 03:12.559
flashing lights,
big name entertainers

03:12.593 --> 03:14.194
and show girls
in skimpy costumes.

03:15.028 --> 03:16.830
You're right, let's pack.

03:16.863 --> 03:18.565
♪ Di di di di ♪

03:18.599 --> 03:19.766
♪ Da di da da da di ♪

03:19.800 --> 03:21.835
♪ Hey hey hey hey ♪

03:21.868 --> 03:23.970
♪ Hey ♪

03:24.004 --> 03:25.371
Balki

03:25.405 --> 03:26.773
we have the opportunity

03:26.807 --> 03:29.475
to own the world's
greatest refrigerator.

03:29.510 --> 03:31.411
It even talks to you.

03:31.444 --> 03:33.413
It tells you when you
leave the door open.

03:33.446 --> 03:34.981
It tells you're
low on eggs.

03:35.015 --> 03:37.383
When you eat too much,
it talks down to you.

03:38.719 --> 03:40.621
I want to go to Vegas.

03:42.422 --> 03:43.757
Well, my name was
on the entry too

03:43.790 --> 03:45.626
and I want
the refrigerator.

03:47.327 --> 03:49.863
But cousin, I never
thought I'd come to America

03:49.896 --> 03:51.031
and here I am.

03:51.064 --> 03:53.600
And now,
I have a chance

03:53.634 --> 03:55.301
to‐to have
an adventure.

03:55.335 --> 03:58.304
To go one of the most famous
place in the world.

03:58.338 --> 04:01.775
And‐and you want
a refrigerator?

04:01.808 --> 04:03.644
It has a lettuce crisper.

04:05.378 --> 04:07.981
Cousin, I know
a way to decide.

04:08.014 --> 04:10.584
Put you hands
out like this.

04:10.617 --> 04:12.452
In Mypos, this how
the parents choose

04:12.485 --> 04:13.720
a bride for their son.

04:16.422 --> 04:18.358
♪ Dimbodega dimbodega ♪

04:18.391 --> 04:19.826
♪ Dabodega smack ♪

04:19.860 --> 04:21.661
♪ Bobedega dimbodega ♪

04:21.695 --> 04:22.729
♪ Bimbodega hack ♪

04:25.666 --> 04:26.667
♪ Ha.. ♪

04:29.736 --> 04:32.839
That's a ridiculous way
to decide anything.

04:32.873 --> 04:34.708
That's what the groom
usually say.

04:38.545 --> 04:39.846
This is America.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.481
In America, we decide
these things

04:41.515 --> 04:42.949
by the flip of a coin.

04:42.983 --> 04:46.019
Now, you call it.
Heads.

04:46.052 --> 04:46.987
Drat.

04:49.389 --> 04:50.423
I lose.

04:50.456 --> 04:51.391
I always lose.

04:51.424 --> 04:53.393
Vegas.

04:53.426 --> 04:55.796
Here we come.

04:55.829 --> 04:57.698
Oh, cousin, we're going
to have an adventure.

04:57.731 --> 04:59.032
Well, I'll go.

04:59.065 --> 05:01.001
But I won't have any fun.

05:01.034 --> 05:02.736
But of course not.

05:02.769 --> 05:04.004
I wouldn't expect you to.

05:07.674 --> 05:10.410
[instrumental music]

05:26.159 --> 05:28.729
It's everything
I dreamed Vegas would be.

05:31.431 --> 05:32.398
Me too.

05:36.002 --> 05:37.403
Oh, look.

05:37.437 --> 05:39.806
Somebody left
a beautiful pen.

05:41.041 --> 05:42.576
It's from the hotel.
You can keep it.

05:42.609 --> 05:43.677
[scoffs]

05:48.982 --> 05:51.918
Look, free champagne.

05:51.952 --> 05:53.720
Sure, they want
you to get drunk

05:53.754 --> 05:54.988
so you'll gamble more.

05:55.021 --> 05:58.024
Don't touch this until
we get back to Chicago.

05:58.058 --> 05:59.793
Now, I'm gonna put
my luggage in my room

05:59.826 --> 06:01.161
'and get a good night's sleep'

06:01.194 --> 06:03.496
'cause tomorrow
is a big day.'

06:18.645 --> 06:20.480
Now, that's great art.

06:26.753 --> 06:28.689
The whole village
could sleep on this.

06:33.560 --> 06:36.630
"Magic fingers,
25 cents."

06:43.904 --> 06:45.038
[buzzing]

07:10.797 --> 07:12.432
Vegas.

07:22.709 --> 07:24.511
Cousin Larry, come here.

07:26.146 --> 07:27.213
Don't tell me.

07:27.247 --> 07:28.615
You found the stationary.

07:30.684 --> 07:32.218
Wayne Newton is here.

07:33.920 --> 07:35.622
So?

07:35.656 --> 07:38.592
He is the biggest selling
record artist on Mypos.

07:38.625 --> 07:40.794
The man is a legend.

07:40.827 --> 07:42.963
We must go see him.

07:42.996 --> 07:47.000
♪ Dankeschoen darling
dankeschoen ♪

07:47.033 --> 07:48.802
♪ Thank you for.. ♪

07:52.973 --> 07:54.775
Okay.

07:54.808 --> 07:57.043
If it means that much to you,
we'll try to get tickets.

07:57.077 --> 07:58.712
Thank you.

07:58.745 --> 07:59.946
Is there anything
you would like to do

07:59.980 --> 08:02.248
while we're here in Vegas?

08:02.282 --> 08:05.619
Well, I did make a list
of some fun things to do.

08:05.652 --> 08:06.887
I thought at 11

08:06.920 --> 08:07.788
we could take the bus tour

08:07.821 --> 08:10.156
out to Hover dam.

08:10.190 --> 08:11.792
That'll get us
back here by 4:30

08:11.825 --> 08:12.959
then it's a 15 minute walk

08:12.993 --> 08:15.161
to the Liberace museum.

08:15.195 --> 08:17.197
Now, for the tour,
if we, uh skip

08:17.230 --> 08:17.831
the shoe collection.

08:19.800 --> 08:21.234
And then we can end the day

08:21.267 --> 08:23.737
with a nice desert walk.

08:23.770 --> 08:24.871
Cousin Larry,
you are leaving out

08:24.905 --> 08:26.039
the most fun thing of all.

08:26.072 --> 08:27.541
The casino.

08:27.574 --> 08:28.742
No, no.

08:28.775 --> 08:30.877
Absolutely, no casinos.

08:30.911 --> 08:32.145
Why not?

08:32.178 --> 08:35.148
Balki, why do you
think I came along?

08:35.181 --> 08:36.950
To take all the fun
out of the trip.

08:39.052 --> 08:40.721
To protect you.

08:40.754 --> 08:43.023
I just don't want you to
end up like our Uncle Pete.

08:43.056 --> 08:46.226
‐ Who Uncle Pete?
‐ Uncle Pete was a gambler.

08:46.259 --> 08:47.861
He gambled away
everything he owned.

08:47.894 --> 08:48.962
His car, his house

08:48.995 --> 08:50.731
we never did find
Aunt Susan.

08:52.098 --> 08:54.100
My point is, it's in
the family blood.

08:54.134 --> 08:56.202
And that's why you can't
go into a casino.

08:56.236 --> 08:58.204
[sobbing]

08:58.238 --> 08:59.973
I want to go to casino.

09:03.243 --> 09:05.746
Alright, maybe..

09:05.779 --> 09:06.880
...after the desert walk

09:06.913 --> 09:08.281
and before Wayne Newton

09:08.314 --> 09:09.750
we can walk through the casino.

09:09.783 --> 09:11.017
Oh, boy.

09:11.051 --> 09:12.085
But no stopping.

09:12.118 --> 09:14.020
Oh, boy.

09:16.156 --> 09:18.625
We should have taken
the refrigerator.

09:18.659 --> 09:22.062
Well, it's a little
late for that now.

09:29.736 --> 09:31.938
[instrumental music]

09:31.972 --> 09:33.840
[indistinct chattering]

09:33.874 --> 09:35.108
(male #1)
'Place your bets.'

09:35.141 --> 09:36.009
(female #1)
'Do it, again.
Do it, again.'

09:36.042 --> 09:37.911
'Whoo.'

09:37.944 --> 09:39.345
(male #2)
'Do it.'

09:39.379 --> 09:40.714
What‐what is this?

09:40.747 --> 09:42.115
This is the bar.

09:42.148 --> 09:44.217
But, what was that
we just ran through?

09:44.250 --> 09:45.619
That was the casino.

09:47.053 --> 09:48.922
Cousin, why‐why
you didn't tell me?

09:48.955 --> 09:51.725
I want to see the casino.

09:51.758 --> 09:54.227
Hey, you got a great view
from right here. Look at them.

09:54.260 --> 09:56.863
You wanna become one of those
miserable souls out there?

09:56.897 --> 09:59.399
[people cheering]

09:59.432 --> 10:01.201
Yes.

10:01.234 --> 10:02.302
No, you don't.

10:02.335 --> 10:04.237
They're really crying
on the inside.

10:04.270 --> 10:07.007
[people cheering]

10:07.040 --> 10:09.409
Boy, they're hiding
it well.

10:09.442 --> 10:10.376
Balki, you just sit down

10:10.410 --> 10:12.145
order a drink and I'll
go get our tickets.

10:12.178 --> 10:15.181
‐ But I want to‐‐
‐ Balki, sit.

10:15.215 --> 10:16.382
Stay.

10:16.416 --> 10:17.417
Stay.

10:17.450 --> 10:19.185
Ah.

10:19.219 --> 10:22.322
Remember Uncle Pete.

10:22.355 --> 10:23.724
‐ 'No more breaks.'
‐ 'Yes, sir.'

10:30.697 --> 10:31.798
Hi, there.

10:32.833 --> 10:35.435
Wanna have a good time?

10:35.468 --> 10:38.104
Well, I've already been
to the Liberace museum.

10:41.074 --> 10:43.376
Let's start again.

10:43.409 --> 10:45.746
Hi, my name's Wendy.

10:45.779 --> 10:47.080
Hello, Wendy.

10:49.449 --> 10:51.084
Are you a show girl?

10:51.117 --> 10:52.853
I can do Hamlet
in a rubber suit

10:52.886 --> 10:54.220
if the price is right.

10:56.857 --> 10:58.124
I love the theater.

10:59.860 --> 11:02.162
Look, so do you wanna
party or what?

11:02.195 --> 11:03.930
Oh, I'd love
to go to a party.

11:03.964 --> 11:05.732
Can I bring cousin Larry?

11:05.766 --> 11:08.234
I got the tickets.

11:08.268 --> 11:10.336
Cousin Larry, this is Wendy.

11:12.172 --> 11:13.874
Hello, Cousin Larry.

11:14.875 --> 11:16.142
Hello, Wendy.

11:18.311 --> 11:21.047
Balki, what are you doing
with this woman?

11:21.081 --> 11:22.883
Shooting the breeze.

11:26.152 --> 11:27.320
She wants to
go to a party.

11:27.353 --> 11:29.289
I bet she does.

11:29.322 --> 11:30.924
Uh..

11:30.957 --> 11:32.959
...this man has no money.

11:34.327 --> 11:35.328
Hi, there.

11:35.361 --> 11:36.863
Wanna have a good time?

11:40.000 --> 11:41.367
Balki..

11:41.401 --> 11:43.336
...what were you
doing with her?

11:43.369 --> 11:45.438
Don't you know what that
woman does for a living?

11:45.471 --> 11:47.874
Well, of course I do.

11:47.908 --> 11:49.142
Don't be ridiculous.

11:51.477 --> 11:53.446
She does Hamlet
in a rubber suit.

11:58.785 --> 12:00.887
No?

12:00.921 --> 12:02.388
Oh, let's just say that uh..

12:02.422 --> 12:05.225
...she's in the world's
oldest profession, hm.

12:05.258 --> 12:07.794
‐ Oh.
‐ Oh.

12:07.828 --> 12:09.262
Oh‐ohh.

12:11.497 --> 12:12.999
She's a sheepherder.

12:16.537 --> 12:19.205
That's right.

12:19.239 --> 12:20.941
Why don't you and I
go get ready for the show?

12:20.974 --> 12:22.242
Oh, we have
plenty of time.

12:22.275 --> 12:24.911
I have...a quarter.

12:24.945 --> 12:27.147
I want to hit the slots.

12:29.516 --> 12:33.153
Alright. This will
be a good lesson for you.

12:33.186 --> 12:34.454
Obviously, you won't
be happy

12:34.487 --> 12:36.256
until you throw
your money away.

12:36.289 --> 12:37.991
Go ahead, put your money
in the machine

12:38.024 --> 12:39.325
pull the handle

12:39.359 --> 12:41.094
watch your money disappear
into the pockets

12:41.127 --> 12:43.429
of some man named Guido.

12:43.463 --> 12:45.131
There, I hope you're happy.

12:45.165 --> 12:46.867
[bell ringing]

12:48.535 --> 12:50.370
I love Vegas.

12:57.110 --> 12:59.980
[instrumental music]

13:00.013 --> 13:01.948
[indistinct chattering]

13:07.220 --> 13:10.390
So, this is what a
casino looks like.

13:11.892 --> 13:13.259
Different when
you're not running.

13:15.061 --> 13:16.429
Okay, you've seen it.

13:16.462 --> 13:18.398
Now let's get out of here.
This place is dangerous.

13:18.431 --> 13:20.500
If you stay here,
you'll catch the fever.

13:20.534 --> 13:22.102
What fever?

13:22.135 --> 13:24.304
I hit $150 jackpot.

13:24.337 --> 13:26.840
Balki, I forbid you
to stay here.

13:26.873 --> 13:28.975
Well, papa, don't preach.

13:32.946 --> 13:35.982
I'm a big boy now.
I can look after myself.

13:36.016 --> 13:38.051
That's just what
Uncle Pete said

13:38.084 --> 13:40.053
just before he gambled
away his pacemaker.

13:41.955 --> 13:44.090
Cousin, I am going
to go gambling.

13:44.124 --> 13:46.026
Alright, alright.
Fine.

13:46.059 --> 13:47.528
This will be
a good lesson.

13:47.561 --> 13:48.895
You've had the thrill
of victory

13:48.929 --> 13:50.531
you should taste
the agony of defeat.

13:56.436 --> 13:58.138
What is this game?

13:58.171 --> 13:59.339
It's called roulette.

13:59.372 --> 14:00.541
The odds are
really against you.

14:00.574 --> 14:02.475
Why don't you try it?

14:02.509 --> 14:05.512
Alright, if you
think I should.

14:05.546 --> 14:09.449
♪ Dimbodega dimbodega
dabodega.. ♪

14:09.482 --> 14:11.384
‐ Just put them down.
‐ Okay.

14:13.386 --> 14:14.588
Good, 32.

14:14.621 --> 14:16.389
Now, watch
your money disappear.

14:19.025 --> 14:20.527
Number 32.

14:23.329 --> 14:25.065
This is fun.

14:25.098 --> 14:26.967
Can you teach me how
to spin the marble?

14:27.000 --> 14:28.268
No.

14:30.504 --> 14:32.506
Bets.

14:32.539 --> 14:34.040
Alright, we don't
have much time

14:34.074 --> 14:35.509
if we wanna see
Wayne Newton.

14:35.542 --> 14:37.343
I'm gonna have to help you
lose your money.

14:37.377 --> 14:38.044
How much
should we bet?

14:38.078 --> 14:39.345
You bet half
and I'll bet half.

14:39.379 --> 14:40.413
That way, one bad spin

14:40.446 --> 14:43.083
and you'll be broke
and miserable.

14:43.116 --> 14:44.450
Good strategy.

14:45.485 --> 14:47.688
Number 36.

14:47.721 --> 14:49.122
Cousin, you won.

14:49.155 --> 14:50.323
I can't get a break.

14:54.127 --> 14:56.029
Oh, I lose.

14:56.062 --> 14:58.599
Now, how do you feel?

14:58.632 --> 15:03.469
‐ Broke and...miserable.
‐ Good.

15:03.504 --> 15:06.973
Believe me, you're a better
person for it.

15:07.007 --> 15:08.208
Now, soon as I lose
the rest of your money

15:08.241 --> 15:10.143
we can go to the show.

15:10.176 --> 15:11.211
Let it ride.

15:16.082 --> 15:18.251
Number 36.

15:19.452 --> 15:21.287
Cousin, you did
pretty good.

15:21.321 --> 15:23.489
Yeah, I guess I would be,
if I was trying to win.

15:26.126 --> 15:27.427
Let's try my birthday.

15:31.064 --> 15:33.399
Cousin, almost time
for Wayne show.

15:33.433 --> 15:34.601
No, Balki,
I can't leave.

15:34.635 --> 15:36.703
I still have this money
to lose for you.

15:36.737 --> 15:38.171
But, Wayne is waiting.

15:38.204 --> 15:39.540
Alright, I‐I‐I'll
tell you what.

15:39.573 --> 15:41.141
Here's your ticket
to the show.

15:41.174 --> 15:43.309
I'll catch up with you
as soon as I lose this.

15:44.545 --> 15:46.079
Number 24.

15:46.112 --> 15:47.280
I win. I win.

15:50.016 --> 15:51.284
Are you sure
you don't mind?

15:51.317 --> 15:52.418
Hmm?

15:54.755 --> 15:56.489
Cousin, are you alright?

15:56.523 --> 15:59.359
I'm fine.
I'll see you at the show.

15:59.392 --> 16:01.161
‐ Why don't you come now?
‐ No, you go ahead.

16:01.194 --> 16:02.563
Save my seat.

16:02.596 --> 16:04.698
I'm just as excited
about seeing Wayne as you are.

16:07.400 --> 16:10.070
♪ Dankeschoen.. ♪

16:14.040 --> 16:16.309
Okay, baby needs
a new pair of shoes.

16:16.342 --> 16:18.745
Double down, boxcars,
let it ride.

16:18.779 --> 16:21.114
Number 24, again.

16:21.147 --> 16:22.415
Yes, yes.

16:31.658 --> 16:34.427
Come on, 12.
Lucky number 12.

16:35.796 --> 16:38.264
Number 22.

16:41.201 --> 16:42.435
I was gonna bet 22.

16:44.437 --> 16:46.039
Okay, give me 22.

16:49.475 --> 16:51.311
‐ Cousin.
‐ What, what?

16:51.344 --> 16:53.079
I waited and waited
for you.

16:53.113 --> 16:55.448
And‐and‐and,
and I worried for you.

16:55.481 --> 16:57.083
Why you didn't come
to see Wayne?

16:57.117 --> 16:58.685
Well, I would have
but I, uh..

16:58.719 --> 17:00.353
I uh, I sold my ticket.

17:00.386 --> 17:02.488
Number 12.

17:07.127 --> 17:10.531
Okay, come on.
Give me six, twelve

17:10.564 --> 17:13.465
twenty two
and all the blacks.

17:15.435 --> 17:17.369
Why you sold your ticket?

17:17.403 --> 17:19.239
Gambling takes money.

17:19.271 --> 17:20.641
Well, you have
plenty of money.

17:20.674 --> 17:23.276
You can never
have enough money.

17:23.309 --> 17:24.744
Cousin, I'm confused.

17:24.778 --> 17:27.280
I thought, you stayed here
to lose my money

17:27.313 --> 17:28.281
to teach me a lesson.

17:28.314 --> 17:30.717
Well, school's out.

17:30.751 --> 17:32.586
Come on, six,
twelve, twenty two

17:32.619 --> 17:34.254
and all the blacks.

17:34.287 --> 17:36.557
Number seven.

17:37.658 --> 17:39.192
Red.

17:45.131 --> 17:47.300
Cousin, where
you got those chips?

17:47.333 --> 17:48.502
I sold my plane ticket.

17:49.736 --> 17:52.506
You sold your plane ticket?

17:52.539 --> 17:54.207
How are you going
to get home?

17:54.240 --> 17:55.408
Don't worry.

17:55.441 --> 17:57.844
When I win enough,
I can buy it back.

17:57.878 --> 18:00.180
I think you take after
Uncle Pete's side of the family.

18:00.213 --> 18:01.314
Okay.

18:01.347 --> 18:02.749
One more time
for number 12.

18:02.783 --> 18:04.384
No, no.
I‐I don't let you do that.

18:04.417 --> 18:05.886
No, Balki, just put
those on the 12.

18:05.919 --> 18:07.854
‐ No, no.
‐ No, Balki, wait.

18:07.888 --> 18:09.523
Oh, look,
there's Wayne Newton.

18:09.556 --> 18:11.391
‐ Wayne.
‐ Everything on the 12.

18:11.424 --> 18:12.526
Spin it. Spin it.

18:13.794 --> 18:15.195
You tricked Balki.

18:15.228 --> 18:17.497
You used Wayne's
name in vain.

18:17.531 --> 18:18.632
I can't let you
gamble away

18:18.665 --> 18:20.534
everything like
your Uncle Pete.

18:28.374 --> 18:29.843
Balki..

18:29.876 --> 18:32.646
...why don't you the nice men
back their marble?

18:35.215 --> 18:37.884
Not until you promise
to stop gambling.

18:37.918 --> 18:39.252
Uh..

18:39.285 --> 18:42.589
He just doesn't understand
good, clean fun.

18:42.623 --> 18:44.224
Promise.

18:44.257 --> 18:45.458
I promise.

18:47.193 --> 18:48.695
Alright, good.

18:53.634 --> 18:57.871
Don't you ever,
ever do that again.

18:57.904 --> 18:59.472
I won't.

18:59.506 --> 19:01.241
Now, go to your room.

19:02.776 --> 19:05.679
I'm not going anywhere.
I lied.

19:05.712 --> 19:07.814
Well, then,
I lied too.

19:07.848 --> 19:09.916
Balki, give me back
those chips.

19:09.950 --> 19:11.852
Number 12.

19:11.885 --> 19:14.354
No, no.

19:14.387 --> 19:16.322
Balki. Balki.

19:24.330 --> 19:26.833
Here's, Larry.

19:32.573 --> 19:35.676
I want my money.

19:43.449 --> 19:45.752
Aah. Aah.

19:48.989 --> 19:51.658
It's alright.

19:51.692 --> 19:54.628
Everything's alright.

19:54.661 --> 19:57.297
I forgive you.

19:57.330 --> 19:59.966
Aah.

20:03.770 --> 20:04.805
I know you're here.

20:04.838 --> 20:05.806
[sniffing]

20:09.510 --> 20:11.745
I can smell my chips.

20:20.554 --> 20:21.454
Whoa, oh‐oh‐oh.

20:21.487 --> 20:23.790
Well..

20:23.824 --> 20:28.261
...maybe, he's not here,
after all.

20:29.395 --> 20:31.264
[grunting]

20:45.846 --> 20:47.313
[buzzing]

20:50.584 --> 20:51.752
[grunting]

20:51.785 --> 20:54.354
Give me my chips.

20:58.592 --> 20:59.926
[Larry panting]

21:03.396 --> 21:06.432
[grunting]

21:06.466 --> 21:07.934
Cousin Larry.
Cousin Larry.

21:07.968 --> 21:09.870
There is no Cousin Larry.

21:09.903 --> 21:12.005
There's only Lucky Larry.

21:12.038 --> 21:14.541
And I'm going
for the big jackpot.

21:14.575 --> 21:16.877
I'm gonna blow
this town wide open.

21:16.910 --> 21:19.813
Now, give me my chips.

21:19.846 --> 21:21.347
You don't know
what you're doing.

21:21.381 --> 21:23.750
I know exactly
what I'm doing.

21:23.784 --> 21:24.851
[breathing heavily]

21:28.522 --> 21:29.590
Uncle Pete.

21:32.593 --> 21:34.394
Uh.
Oh, my God.

21:37.631 --> 21:38.699
What's happening?

21:38.732 --> 21:40.500
Well, I'm no expert.

21:43.837 --> 21:46.740
But as far as I can tell..

21:46.773 --> 21:48.875
...you just went off
the deep end.

21:50.911 --> 21:52.746
I don't know what's happening
to me.

21:52.779 --> 21:54.648
I‐I thought I came along
to protect you.

21:54.681 --> 21:57.117
And, uh, now look at me.

21:57.150 --> 21:58.919
I sold my
Wayne Newton ticket.

21:58.952 --> 22:00.486
I sold my plane ticket.

22:01.955 --> 22:03.389
I sold the free champagne.

22:07.661 --> 22:08.695
I'm..

22:09.863 --> 22:12.398
I'm a compulsive gambler

22:12.432 --> 22:13.033
Uh..

22:15.502 --> 22:17.137
No, you're not.

22:17.170 --> 22:19.740
You're just a regular person
who got caught up

22:19.773 --> 22:21.441
in the excitement
of Vegas.

22:23.610 --> 22:25.411
Am I?

22:25.445 --> 22:27.413
Well, of course you are.

22:27.447 --> 22:29.716
Well, you don't bet
on the football pools

22:29.750 --> 22:31.084
or the horses at home,
do you?

22:31.117 --> 22:32.385
That's true.

22:32.418 --> 22:35.021
And when I try to buy
a lottery ticket..

22:35.055 --> 22:36.557
...you told me not
to waste my money.

22:36.590 --> 22:37.691
I did, I did.

22:39.626 --> 22:40.961
Do you feel
like gambling now?

22:42.162 --> 22:43.730
I don't ever wanna
see the inside

22:43.764 --> 22:46.700
of another casino
for as long as I live.

22:46.733 --> 22:49.536
Oh, you're doing
it again.

22:49.570 --> 22:51.572
Oh, yeah,
yeah, yeah.

22:51.605 --> 22:53.139
[speaksing foreign language]

23:11.157 --> 23:11.925
Come again?

23:14.194 --> 23:17.063
You're problem is,
you either go too far

23:17.097 --> 23:19.165
or you don't go at all.

23:19.199 --> 23:20.867
If you want to have any fun

23:20.901 --> 23:22.969
you've got to find somewhere
in the middle.

23:25.005 --> 23:26.807
I've always had trouble
with the middle.

23:29.109 --> 23:31.945
Cousin, you just need
some practice having fun.

23:31.978 --> 23:34.180
I could help you.

23:34.214 --> 23:37.884
For instance, this weekend
we could have little fun.

23:37.918 --> 23:41.622
Then next weekend, we could
have a little more fun.

23:41.655 --> 23:43.557
And then in a couple of years

23:43.590 --> 23:46.126
you could be a real
party animal..

23:46.159 --> 23:47.027
...like me.

23:47.994 --> 23:49.095
Do you think so?

23:49.129 --> 23:52.232
Well, of course I do.

23:52.265 --> 23:54.535
And don't worry
about your plane ticket.

23:54.568 --> 23:57.604
‐ I'll loan you the money.
‐ Oh, Balki, thank you.

23:57.638 --> 24:00.206
I owe you a lot.

24:00.240 --> 24:02.543
I know.

24:02.576 --> 24:04.077
But you would do
the same for me.

24:04.110 --> 24:06.446
I would?
I would. I would.

24:08.715 --> 24:09.983
That's nice.

24:11.284 --> 24:13.954
Now, let's go
do something fun.

24:13.987 --> 24:15.956
Can we catch Wayne Newton's
second show?

24:15.989 --> 24:17.924
Now, you're talking.

24:17.958 --> 24:20.994
Larry Appleton, you're going
to be one fun guy.

24:22.629 --> 24:23.930
♪ Dankeschoen.. ♪

24:23.964 --> 24:26.667
[sings in foreign language]

24:31.538 --> 24:33.039
♪ When you tore your dress ♪
♪ When you tore your dress ♪

24:33.073 --> 24:34.575
♪ What a mess ♪
♪ What a mess.. ♪

24:34.608 --> 24:36.142
[instrumental music]

24:38.679 --> 24:40.947
[theme music]

25:00.166 --> 25:03.103
[music continues]
